          "instruction": "Based on your knowledge of computer hardware and software, fill in the blanks to describe the role of the CPU in processing data. Use terms from the learning cards and flashcards.",
          "codeTemplate": "The ___ is the 'brain' of the computer, responsible for executing instructions and performing calculations. It works closely with ___ to temporarily store data.",
          "options": [
            "RAM",
            "CPU",
            "Input Devices",
            "Operating System"
          ],
          "correctAnswer": "CPU,RAM",
          "explanation": "The CPU executes instructions, and RAM provides temporary storage for the data being processed."
        },
        {
          "instruction": "Using your understanding of input and output, complete the sentence about how users interact with a computer. Refer to the 'How a Computer Works Essentials' learning card.",
          "codeTemplate": "___ allow you to send instructions and data to the computer, while the computer displays results through ___.",
          "options": [
            "Input Devices",
            "Output Devices",
            "Storage Devices",
            "Processing Units"
          ],
          "correctAnswer": "Input Devices,Output Devices",
          "explanation": "Input devices like keyboards and mice send data to the computer, and output devices like monitors display the results."
        },
        {
          "instruction": "Based on the Interactive Coding example, fill in the blanks to describe the flow of data in a simple program.",
          "codeTemplate": "First, the program receives ___ from the user. Then, it performs ___ on the data. Finally, it displays the ___.",
          "options": [
            "processing",
            "output",
            "input",
            "storage"
          ],
          "correctAnswer": "input,processing,output",
          "explanation": "The basic flow is: Input (getting data), Processing (manipulating data), and Output (displaying results)."
        }
      ]
    }
  }
